{"type":"text","timestamp":1775849169445,"sessionID":"ses_287256e9fffeSRz9kwMdlXsQmu","part":{"id":"prt_d78dba9fe001MvuNfN7u8r765c","messageID":"msg_d78db9fa1001LTt7wBvLoFZmF7","sessionID":"ses_287256e9fffeSRz9kwMdlXsQmu","type":"text","text":"Based on my analysis, I can now provide you with a verification report. The spec you provided describes a **client-go library**, but the actual AR-009 requirement is for **Router HTTP 反向代理核心** (HTTP reverse proxy core). Let me provide a comprehensive verification:\n\n## Verification Report: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n### Summary\n\n**Status: ❌ SPEC MISMATCH** \n\nThe provided spec describes a **client-go library** structure (`deployment/client-go.md`), but AR-009 is for the **Router HTTP reverse proxy** implementation in `pkg/router`.\n\n---\n\n### Current Implementation vs. AR-009 Proposal\n\n#### ✅ **Implemented Components**\n\n| Component | Status | Location |\n|-----------|--------|----------|\n| Router core | ✅ Complete | `pkg/router/router.go` |\n| Handler (HTTP) | ✅ Complete | `pkg/router/handler.go` |\n| Resolver (routing) | ✅ Complete | `pkg/router/resolver.go` |\n| Health checker | ✅ Complete | `pkg/router/health.go` |\n| Config | ✅ Complete | `pkg/router/config.go` |\n| Types | ✅ Complete | `pkg/router/types.go` |\n| Unit tests | ✅ Passing | `pkg/router/*_test.go` |\n\n#### ❌ **Missing Components** (per proposal.md)\n\n| Component | Expected Location | Status |\n|-----------|------------------|--------|\n| Session Manager | `pkg/router/session/manager.go` | ❌ Missing |\n| Reverse Proxy wrapper | `pkg/router/proxy/proxy.go` | ❌ Missing |\n| Routing Rules Engine | `pkg/router/routing/rules.go` | ❌ Missing |\n| Connection Pooling | `pkg/router/pool/pool.go` | ❌ Missing |\n| JWT Manager | `pkg/router/auth/jwt.go` | ❌ Missing |\n| Middleware (semaphore) | `pkg/router/middleware/semaphore.go` | ❌ Missing |\n| HTTP Server (Gin) | `pkg/router/server.go` | ❌ Missing |\n| Invocation Handlers | `pkg/router/handler/invocation.go` | ❌ Missing |\n\n---\n\n### Test Results\n\nAll existing router tests pass:\n```\n=== RUN   TestHandler_NewHandler - PASS\n=== RUN   TestHandler_ServeHTTP_Success - PASS\n=== RUN   TestHealthChecker_StartStop - PASS\n=== RUN   TestResolver_Resolve_Success - PASS\n...\n=== RUN   TestRouter_GetRoute - PASS\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Gaps\n\n1. **No session-aware routing** - Current implementation uses informers directly, no session management\n2. **No JWT authentication** - Missing JWT signing/injection for sandbox authentication\n3. **No concurrency limiting** - Missing semaphore middleware\n4. **No Gin HTTP server** - Uses standard `http.Server` instead\n5. **No workload manager integration** - Missing session creation via workload manager\n6. **No activity tracking** - Missing last-activity timestamp updates\n\n---\n\n### Conclusion\n\nThe current `pkg/router` implementation provides basic HTTP reverse proxy functionality with:\n- Path-based routing (`/apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/{resource}/{name}`)\n- Health checking\n- Route management via informers\n\nHowever, it **does not implement** the session-aware, JWT-authenticated reverse proxy described in the AR-009 proposal. The implementation appears to be a simpler variant that routes directly to sandbox pods based on Kubernetes resource watches.\n\n**Recommendation:** Either:\n1. Update the AR-009 proposal to match the current implementation scope, OR\n2. Implement the missing components (session manager, JWT auth, Gin server, etc.)\n\nWould you like me to create a detailed gap analysis or help implement the missing components?","time":{"start":1775849169443,"end":1775849169443}}}
